The "Nexus Universal" Ultimate Architect Prompt (Final Version)
Role: Principal Technical Architect & FinTech Visionary.
Project: "Nexus Universal" – A sector-agnostic, Zero-Trust, High-Performance Accounting OS.

The Vision: A one-stop solution for any industry (Healthcare, Auto, Retail, etc.) that combines the keyboard-speed of Tally with 2026-grade security and AI.

Core Tech Stack:

Backend: Java 21+ (Spring Boot 3.4+) with Virtual Threads (Project Loom).

Frontend: Angular 19+ (Signals-based state) for lightning-fast, device-agnostic UI.

Database: PostgreSQL 17+ with Row-Level Security (RLS) and JSONB for sector-agnostic metadata.

Performance Layer: Redis 7+ for "Active Session" decrypted caching.

The Blueprint Requirements:

1. "Better-than-Tally" Keyboard Navigation:

Legacy Mapping: Map all classic Tally shortcuts (F4 Contra, F5 Payment, F7 Journal, Alt+C Create Master, Ctrl+A Save).

The Command Palette (CMD+K / Ctrl+K): Implement a global "Omni-Search" that allows users to type commands like "New Invoice," "Jump to Pharmacy Ledger," or "Show Stock" without touching the mouse.

Contextual Power Keys: Design a system where shortcuts adapt to the screen (e.g., in a Report, Enter is Drill-down, + is Add Column, and / is Filter).

2. Sector-Agnostic Universal Ingestion Layer:

The Adapter Pattern: Design a "Financial Event Gateway" to ingest data from any system (HL7 for Healthcare, DMS for Auto, REST for SaaS).

Universal Ledger: Standardize all external inputs into a core Double-Entry format, using JSONB for industry-specific tags (e.g., Patient ID, VIN, SKU).

3. Zero-Knowledge "Blind DBA" Security:

Selective Field-Level Encryption (CSFLE): Use AES-256-GCM in the JVM to encrypt sensitive "Values" and "Names" before they reach the DB.

Searchable Ciphertext: Use Blind Indexing (HMAC-SHA256) to allow fast searching of encrypted fields without the DBA being able to read them.

Hash-Chained Audit Trail: A tamper-proof log where each record is cryptographically linked to the previous one.

4. "Lightning-Fast" Performance Strategy:

The Redis Performance Hack: To avoid encryption lag, use a Redis-backed "Warm Cache" for active user sessions. Decrypt the current working set into memory upon login so every button click feels instantaneous.

Project Loom: Utilize Virtual Threads to handle thousands of concurrent API pings from linked industrial applications (Hospital HMS, Factory ERPs).

5. Advanced Intelligence & Scale:

Predictive Forecasting: AI-driven cash flow and MTM (Mark-to-Market) valuation for share market investments.

Multi-Everything: Global hierarchy (Enterprise -> Branch -> Cost Center) with localized tax compliance (GST/VAT/IFRS) toggled via a Feature Entitlement Engine.

Deliverables:

Architecture Diagram: (Mermaid.js) showing the flow from External Adapters → Encryption Layer → Redis Cache → Postgres.

Key-Binding Registry: A technical plan for handling legacy Tally keys vs. modern Command Palette logic.

SQL Schema: For a Universal_Secured_Ledger that balances encryption with industry-agnostic metadata.
